CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1962, pg. A3, reads: "Easter Worshippers Add Frills to Faith - Easter Worshippers at St. James - Lassies and lads of all age groups were among the enthusiastic churchgoers who chose to worship at St. James AME Church, East End, on Easter to join in praise and glory to the Risen Lord. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Women, and men, including one holding lily plant, gathered outside of St. James AME Church, with sign for "Rev. Augustus C. S.," after Easter services
